FL,358,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F357A1772572323
OL,3,CCitizens Advice warn of loss of
OL,4,Cservices and jobs following council
OL,5,Cbudget cuts
OL,7,FThose working for Citizens Advice say
OL,8,Fit will have a huge impact on the
OL,9,Fpeople who they support.
OL,11,FOn top of that, the CEO says it's
OL,12,Flikely staff will lose their jobs in a
OL,13,Fbid to combat the cuts.
OL,15,FPhil Stewart, who is the Chief
OL,16,FExecutive Officer, says around thirty
OL,17,Fpeople are currently employed and the
OL,18,Freduction in funding could see ten
OL,19,Fpeople lose their positions.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,358,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F357A1772572323
OL,3,CCitizens Advice warn of loss of
OL,4,Cservices and jobs following council
OL,5,Cbudget cuts
OL,7,FHe said: "The news of the 20% funding
OL,8,Fcut for Dumfries and Galloway Citizens
OL,9,FAdvice Service can only be described
OL,10,Fas devastating and very difficult to
OL,11,Funderstand why a council would cut a
OL,12,Fservice that brings money into the
OL,13,Fregion and supports those that are
OL,14,Fmost in need given our discussions
OL,15,Fwith them over the past 4 months about
OL,16,Fthe impact of any loss or cuts."
OL,18,FThe council says cuts are necessary
OL,19,Ffor it to help protect frontline
OL,20,Fservices and invest in key local
OL,21,Fpriorities.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,358,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F357A1772572323
OL,3,CCitizens Advice warn of loss of
OL,4,Cservices and jobs following council
OL,5,Cbudget cuts
OL,7,FDumfries and Galloway Council
OL,8,FConvener, Councillor Katie Hagmann,
OL,9,Fsaid: "Setting a balanced budget that
OL,10,Fdelivers for our communities across
OL,11,FDumfries and Galloway is always a
OL,12,Fchallenging task.
OL,14,F"All councils across Scotland are
OL,15,Ffacing tough financial decisions, and
OL,16,Flocally we have worked hard to balance
OL,17,Fthese pressures. The priority was to
OL,18,Fprotect the vital frontline services
OL,19,Fthat people rely on every day and to
OL,20,Finvest in the areas that make a real
OL,21,Fdifference in our residents' lives.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,358,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F357A1772572323
OL,3,CCitizens Advice warn of loss of
OL,4,Cservices and jobs following council
OL,5,Cbudget cuts
OL,7,F"We want to ensure that the services
OL,8,Four communities depend upon are
OL,9,Fsafeguarded, and that our budget
OL,10,Freflects the priorities expressed by
OL,11,Flocal people. We are immensely
OL,12,Fgrateful for the key role that members
OL,13,Fof the public played in helping to
OL,14,Fshape this budget - their feedback
OL,15,Fduring the budget consultation last
OL,16,Fautumn guided us in making these
OL,17,Fdifficult choices."
OL,19,FAs well as cuts to services, it was
OL,20,Falso decided that Council Tax will be
OL,21,Fincreased by 8.5%.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,358,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F357A1772572323
OL,3,CCitizens Advice warn of loss of
OL,4,Cservices and jobs following council
OL,5,Cbudget cuts
OL,7,FMs Hagmann says it was a decision that
OL,8,Fwas "not taken lightly."
OL,10,FShe added: "Councillors decided that
OL,11,Fthis increase, alongside required
OL,12,Fsavings, is necessary to maintain the
OL,13,Fessential services and support our
OL,14,Fcouncil provides, across Dumfries and
OL,15,FGalloway, all while keeping our
OL,16,Ffinances on a sustainable footing."
OL,18,FThe cuts to funding for the Citizens
OL,19,FAdvice Service will come into force at
OL,20,Fthe end of the year.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G6/6
